      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis compared against published FDA generic pump experimental measurements at 2500 RPM and 4 L/min. Predicted NIH over-estimates experimental mean by 38%; model error exceeds acceptance threshold for MRL 5.",
      "comparisonMetric": "Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH)",
      "validationStatus": "not-passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-cou2-uq-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ sensitivity study on hemolysis model inputs",
      "description": "Monte Carlo sampling over blood viscosity, pump rotational speed tolerance, and hemolysis model constants. 95th-percentile NIH prediction exceeds absolute clinical threshold at two of five operating points. Large parametric sensitivity to hemolysis model constant C confirms model form gap.",
      "comparisonMetric": "95th-percentile NIH across 5 operating points",
      "validationStatus": "not-passed"
    }
  ],
