      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must match COU operating envelope in fluid properties, rotational speed, and inlet flow waveform within defined tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Published FDA pump experiments used bovine blood with viscosity within 8% of target. Rotational speed tolerance was ±50 RPM, within acceptance bounds. Inlet waveform was steady-state rather than pulsatile VAD waveform — a partial mismatch. Achieved level 3 does not meet required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (e.g., NRMSE, validation uncertainty) must be computed for NIH predictions against experimental data with uncertainty bounds on both simulation and experiment.",
      "rationale": "Qualitative comparison plots were provided; NRMSE was computed but experimental uncertainty was not propagated into the comparison metric. Validation uncertainty U_val was not formally estimated. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
