      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation QoI (NIH) must be the same scalar quantity used in the COU acceptance decision, computed via the same post-processing pathway.",
      "rationale": "NIH is used as both the validation QoI and the COU decision metric. Post-processing pathway is consistent. However, the hemolysis model constant C was recalibrated between the validation study and the COU runs without documented justification, reducing relevance. Achieved level 3 does not meet required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
