      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must cover the full COU operating envelope including pulsatile inlet conditions, Class III device geometry, and patient-representative blood rheology.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry under steady-state conditions using bovine blood. COU requires pulsatile operation of a specific Class III device geometry with human blood rheology. Geometric and flow-condition gaps are substantial. Achieved level 2 is far below required level 5."
