      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence residuals must be below 1e-6 for all transport equations at all operating points; floating-point round-off sensitivity analysis must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was not systematically documented across all five operating points. Round-off sensitivity analysis was not performed. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "An independent analyst must re-execute the simulation workflow from boundary condition specification through post-processing to identify user-introduced errors.",
      "rationale": "No independent re-execution of the simulation workflow was performed. Use error assessment is an epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis power-law model form must be justified against alternative constitutive models (e.g., strain-based, energy dissipation) with sensitivity analysis demonstrating robustness of NIH predictions to model form selection.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was used without comparison to alternative model forms. No model form sensitivity study was conducted. This is the primary epistemic gap identified at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources with uncertainty characterization; Monte Carlo distributions must be justified against patient population data.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with distributions assigned to 6 of 11 input parameters. Remaining 5 parameters were treated as deterministic without justification. Hemolysis model constant C distribution was assumed uniform without literature support. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental validation data must be drawn from a statistically adequate sample of test articles with inter-sample variability characterized; minimum n=5 pump units tested.",
      "rationale": "Published FDA pump data used a single test article per operating condition. Inter-sample variability was not characterized. Sample size is insufficient for MRL 5. Epistemic gap; achieved level 1."
